-- General Electric Becomes Biggest Acquirer With 196 Deals Over Five Years
-- B y   A n n a - L o u i s e   J a c k s o n
-- 2010-10-07T04:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/ge-becomes-world-s-biggest-acquirer-with-196-deals-in-5-years.html
General Electric Co. bought more
companies in the past five years than any other major public
corporation in the world, committing $62.6 billion for 196
acquisitions, according to data compiled by Bloomberg Rankings.  Bloomberg ranked $5 billion-plus public companies by the
number of pending and completed deals announced since September
2005. Private-equity transactions, terminated deals and
acquisitions with multiple buyers were excluded.  A summary of the ranking is below. For the complete list
